foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: In the FY 2017 Annual FOIA Report the number of request pending at the end of FY2017 was 119 reported for PS, it should have been 118.
In the FY2017 Annual FOIA Report the number of request pending at the end of FY2017 was 20 reported for OIG, it should have been 19.
In the FY2017 Annual FOIA Report the number for the agency overall was 162 reported, it should have been 160.

foia:OtherDenialReason.foia:OtherDenialReasonDescriptionText: Unable to Locate or Contact Requester

foia:ProcessedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: In the FY2017 Annual FOIA Report, PS reported the number of requests processed was 1,944, it should have been 1,945.
In the FY2017 Annual FOIA Report, PIS reported the number of requests processed was 449, it should have been 445.
In the FY2017 Annual FOIA Report, the overall agency reported the number of requests processed was 3140, it should have been 3137.

foia:BackloggedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: In FY2017 Annual FOIA Report, the PS number of requests in the backlog at the end of FY2017 was reported as 25, it should have been 23.

In FY2017 Annual FOIA Report, the OIG number of requests in the backlog at the end of FY2017 was reported as 1, it should have been 0. In FY2017 Annual FOIA Report, the agency overall number of requests in the backlog at the end of FY2017 was reported as 39, it should have been 36.
